<subSubSection id="C3036527681ABF15FF50FE951626FEAA" box="[198,1322,271,298]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA636AC681ABF15FF50FE951626FEAA" blockId="68.[198,1322,152,298]" box="[198,1322,271,298]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B96DEABE681ABF15FF50FE95125FFEA9" bold="true" box="[198,339,271,297]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Etymology.</emphasis>
Lat. 
<emphasis id="B96DEABE681ABF15FE06FE8A12D0FEA9" box="[400,476,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">pecten</emphasis>
= brush, specific epithet refers to the brush-like structure on metatibiae.
</paragraph>
